shows.description: Hotel owner Basil Fawlty's incompetence, short fuse, and arrogance form a combination that ensures accidents and trouble are never far away.

shows.title: BoJack Horseman
shows.description: BoJack Horseman was the star of the hit television show "Horsin' Around" in the '80s and '90s, but now he's washed up, living in Hollywood, complaining about everything, and wearing colorful sweaters.

shows.title: Pride and Prejudice
shows.description: While the arrival of wealthy gentlemen sends her marriage-minded mother into a frenzy, willful and opinionated Elizabeth Bennet matches wits with haughty Mr. Darcy.

shows.title: Freaks and Geeks
shows.description: A high school mathlete starts hanging out with a group of burnouts while her younger brother navigates his freshman year.

shows.title: Blackadder Goes Forth
shows.description: Stuck in the middle of World War I, Captain Edmund Blackadder does his best to escape the banality of the war.

shows.title: Twin Peaks
shows.description: An idiosyncratic FBI agent investigates the murder of a young woman in the even more idiosyncratic town of Twin Peaks.

shows.title: Dragon Ball Z
shows.description: With the help of the powerful Dragonballs, a team of fighters led by the saiyan warrior Goku defend the planet earth from extraterrestrial enemies.

shows.title: Narcos
shows.description: A chronicled look at the criminal exploits of Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar, as well as the many other drug kingpins who plagued the country through the years.

shows.title: Chappelle's Show
shows.description: Comedian Dave Chappelle hosts this sketch-comedy show that parodies many of the nuances of race and culture.

shows.title: Black Mirror
shows.description: An anthology series exploring a twisted, high-tech multiverse where humanity's greatest innovations and darkest instincts collide.

shows.title: The Last of Us
shows.description: After a global pandemic destroys civilization, a hardened survivor takes charge of a 14-year-old girl who may be humanity's last hope.

shows.title: I, Claudius
shows.description: The personal and governmental affairs of the Julio-Claudian dynasty at the beginning of the Roman Empire, as recalled by one of its rulers.

shows.title: South Park
shows.description: Follows the misadventures of four irreverent grade-schoolers in the quiet, dysfunctional town of South Park, Colorado.

shows.title: Over the Garden Wall
shows.description: Two brothers find themselves lost in a mysterious land and try to find their way home.

shows.title: Kota Factory

shows.title: Ted Lasso
shows.description: American college football coach Ted Lasso heads to London to manage AFC Richmond, a struggling English Premier League soccer team.

shows.title: Six Feet Under
shows.description: A chronicle of the lives of a dysfunctional family who run an independent funeral home in Los Angeles.

shows.title: Peaky Blinders

shows.title: Rome
shows.description: A down-to-earth account of the lives of both illustrious and ordinary Romans set in the last days of the Roman Republic.

shows.title: Oz
shows.description: A series chronicling the daily activities of an unusual prison facility and its criminal inhabitants.

shows.title: Gullak
shows.description: Set in quaint by-lanes in the heart of India, Gullak is a collection of disarming and relatable tales of the Mishra family.

shows.title: Vinland Saga

shows.title: Steins;Gate
shows.description: After discovering time travel, a university student and his colleagues must use their knowledge of it to stop an evil organization and their diabolical plans.

shows.title: Dark
shows.description: A family saga with a supernatural twist, set in a German town where the disappearance of two young children exposes the relationships among four families.

shows.title: Panchayat

shows.title: The Boys
shows.description: A group of vigilantes set out to take down corrupt superheroes who abuse their superpowers.

shows.title: Fleabag

shows.title: Bleach: Thousand-Year Blood War
shows.description: The peace is suddenly broken when warning sirens blare through the Soul Society. Residents are disappearing without a trace and nobody knows who's behind it. Meanwhile, a darkness is approaching Ichigo and his friends in Karakura Town.

shows.title: Battlestar Galactica
shows.description: When an old enemy, the Cylons, resurface and obliterate the 12 colonies, the crew of the aged Galactica protect a small civilian fleet - the last of humanity - as they journey toward the fabled 13th colony, Earth.

shows.title: The Simpsons
shows.description: The satiric adventures of a working-class family in the misfit city of Springfield.

shows.title: Arrested Development
shows.description: Level-headed son Michael Bluth takes over family affairs after his father is imprisoned. But the rest of his spoiled, dysfunctional family are making his job unbearable.

shows.title: The Shield
shows.description: Drama series following the lives and cases of dirty cop Vic Mackey and the corrupt LAPD unit under his command.

shows.title: Downton Abbey
shows.description: A chronicle of the lives of the British aristocratic Crawley family and their servants in the early twentieth century.

shows.title: House
shows.description: An antisocial maverick doctor who specializes in diagnostic medicine does whatever it takes to solve puzzling cases that come his way using his crack team of doctors and his wits.

shows.title: One Punch Man
shows.description: The story of Saitama, a hero that does it just for fun & can defeat his enemies with a single punch.

shows.title: Invincible
shows.description: An adult animated series based on the Skybound/Image comic about a teenager whose father is the most powerful superhero on the planet.

shows.title: Severance

shows.title: Mad Men
shows.description: A drama about one of New York's most prestigious ad agencies at the beginning of the 1960s, focusing on one of the firm's most mysterious but extremely talented ad executives, Donald Draper.
